com.observability.modeling.probe.descriptor.entities

Class Obsolete_DescriptorElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.observability.modeling.probe.descriptor.entities.Obsolete_DescriptorElement

  • public class Obsolete_DescriptorElement
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an element inside a descriptor file. Below is an example descriptor file (without the annotations) and how it converts to a entity structure ---> Element which has key = "Plugin" and value ="GenericJMX" ---> it has one child which is the element below ObjectName "org.apache.cassandra.metrics:type=Storage,name=Load" ---> this element has key but no value so value == null Type "gauge" ---> this element has no children so children list should be empty. InstancePrefix "data_load" Attribute "Count" Type "gauge" InstancePrefix "data_load" Attribute "Count"
    Author:
    Caglayan "Gem" Gemici
